{"timestamp": "2025-12-12 14:31:20.703258", "event": "llm_start", "messages": "content='Based on the diagnosis report: **Anomaly detected**\\n\\n- All ping tests in the lab are successful **except** those originating from **`host_2_1_1_1`**.  \\n- The ping results for `host_2_1_1_1` show `status: \"unknown\"` for every destination, indicating that the host cannot send or receive ICMP packets.\\n\\n**Faulty device**\\n\\n- `host_2_1_1_1` is the only host that fails to reach any other node.\\n\\n**Root cause**\\n\\n1. **Missing IP configuration**  \\n   - `ifconfig` shows `eth0` is up, but the `ip_addr` output contains no IPv4 address for `eth0`.  \\n   - `ip_route` is empty, meaning the host has no routing table entries.\\n\\n2. Because the host has no IP address, it cannot participate in the network, so all outbound traffic (including ping) fails.\\n\\n**Conclusion**\\n\\n- The problem is isolated to `host_2_1_1_1`.  \\n- The root cause is a mis‑configured or missing IP address on its network interface.  \\n- Fixing the IP assignment (or restoring the network configuration) will restore connectivity., please provide the submission. Do not submit if no report available.' additional_kwargs={} response_metadata={} id='0756521f-3a7e-4a93-ac39-4c6fb1ad032a'", "model": {"lc": 1, "type": "not_implemented", "id": ["langchain_ollama", "chat_models", "ChatOllama"], "repr": "ChatOllama(model='gpt-oss:20b', validate_model_on_init=True, temperature=0.0, base_url='http://10.68.186.140:11434')", "name": "ChatOllama"}}
